This paper discusses the optimization of video content delivery in wireless networks, which involves aspects of network infrastructure, multimedia processing, information theory, distributed computing, and system design. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which covers topics related to the design, analysis, and optimization of communication networks. Other likely sub-categories include cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
